# Browser-sandbox — Environment Variables
#
# Cloud-hosted Chromium driving the virtual_browser embodiment via the
# computer-use-v1 wire format. Per docs/doctrine/motebit-computer.md
# and spec/computer-use-v1.md §8.1.
#
# Quick start (local dev):
#   cd services/browser-sandbox
#   cp .env.example .env             # fill in MOTEBIT_API_TOKEN
#   pnpm browser:install             # one-time Chromium download (~150 MB)
#   pnpm dev                         # starts on :3500
#
# The runtime's CloudBrowserDispatcher (in @motebit/runtime) connects
# here over HTTP. See packages/runtime/src/cloud-browser-dispatcher.ts.

# ─── Required ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Bearer token gating every authed endpoint. Must be >= 16 chars.
# In prod, the relay generates this and rotates per release; the
# dispatcher's getAuthToken callback returns the same value.
MOTEBIT_API_TOKEN=

# ─── Networking ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Server port (default: 3500)
MOTEBIT_PORT=3500

# ─── Pool sizing ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Hard cap on concurrent Chromium sessions across all callers.
# A context is ~150-200 MB; cap prevents a single misuse from OOMing
# the box. Default: 4.
BROWSER_SANDBOX_MAX_SESSIONS=4

# Idle timeout (ms) before a session is auto-disposed by the reaper.
# Frees Chromium contexts whose motebit forgot to dispose. Default: 600000 (10m).
BROWSER_SANDBOX_IDLE_MS=600000

# ─── Viewport ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Logical viewport width × height that the service advertises to every
# session on POST /sessions/ensure. Action coordinates live in this
# space; screenshot dimensions match these values.
BROWSER_SANDBOX_VIEWPORT_WIDTH=1280
BROWSER_SANDBOX_VIEWPORT_HEIGHT=800
